and continue the design and d$$, $$$$, $$The Conventional Prompt Strike (CPS) program is a dual-phased acquisition program currently in the MTA Rapid Fielding phase for initial ZUMWALT fielding. The rapid
fielding path of MTA provides for the fielding of rapidly developed operationally demonstrated capabilities to meet emerging military needs. In FY 2024, the program
conducted a test to prove the end-to-end flight capability of a Blk 1 AUR. In FY 2025, the program executed a test which demonstrated the capability of a cold-gas
launched hypersonic prototype weapon system. The program is currently awaiting post-flight analysis completion for the exit criteria of the Rapid Prototyping phase. The
CPS acquisition program also provides a common AUR for the Army's use in Dark Eagle; end-to-end flight capability from the Dark Eagle launcher was successfully
demonstrated during an Army-led flight test in FY25 to support Army fielding. System design, prototyping, and early fielding utilize the MTA, as authorized by Section

804 of the FY 2016 National Defense Authorization Act (NDAA) and amended in FY 2017 NDAA (codified at 10 U.S.C. sub sec 2302 note), with the goal of transitioning
to a Major Capability Acquisition (MCA) at Milestone C.

