Marine Aviation Demonstration/Validation supports the development of Marine Aviation's future capability concepts as part of Marine Corps Force Design and Marine
Corps Aviation's Project Eagle, progressing these concepts through development, demonstration and ultimately transition into fieldable capabilities This PE funds
development of USMC Vertical Take-Off and Landing (VTOL) capabilities, including manned and unmanned air vehicles, and associated and requisite capabilities.
Through development and prototyping, this PE matures and/or rapidly inserts industry and Government technologies into lethality gaps, enabling a cohesive, warfighter-
centric approach towards a future lethality-based portfolio for Marine Aviation.

JUSTIFICATION FOR BUDGET ACTIVITY: This program is funded under ADVANCED COMPONENT DEVELOPMENT AND PROTOTYPES because it includes all
efforts necessary to evaluate integrated technologies, and representative models or prototype systems in a high fidelity and realistic operating environment.

