Remarks
 Autonomous Amphibious Robotic Vehicles: This funding will accelerate the integration of advanced autonomous software onto existing vehicle platforms and initiate the design
 of a purpose-built, semi-amphibious robotic combat vehicle tailored to the unique demands of Marine Corps littoral operations.

 Containerized Secure Units: Funding will be used to procure initial production units for operational test and evaluation, with a focus on validating deployment speed, energy
 efficiency, and structural integrity in a variety of expeditionary environments.

 Hydrofoiling Wing-In-Ground Effect Prototype: This initiative will fund the development and demonstration of a full-scale prototype to assess the military utility of seaglider
 technology for high-speed, ship-to-shore logistical support and clandestine insertion of small units.

 Secure Communications Support Units: These funds will procure commercially available, accredited secure shelters to serve as a baseline for developing future mobile,
 scalable, and resilient command and control facilities for distributed operations.

