A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The DRAKE Counter Unmanned Aircraft Systems (CUAS) is an Electronic Warfare (EW) Force Protection system designed to detect, identify, track, and defeat small
Unmanned Aircraft Systems (sUAS) for afloat naval forces. The DRAKE system will be upgraded with improved radios, processors, and display units to meet the
non-kinetic requirements established in the OPNAV DRAKE Top Level Requirement (TLR). The program will utilize Commercial Off-The-Shelf (COTS) hardware for
the display and custom, software and hardware in the Increment 1 tech refresh. Increment 1 upgrades will focus on refreshing the core technology to replace legacy
hardware with the latest processors/controllers, which will significantly increase signal processing speed and bandwidth (NextGen SDR). These improvements will
enable the system to counter more advanced commercial sUAS efficiently. A COTS tablet-like Graphical User Interface (GUI) called the Control Display Unit (CDU) 2.0
will replace the legacy CDU, providing enhanced visual tracking and identification data of UAS. This upgrade will ultimately improve situational awareness and signal
analysis for the warfighter. In Increment 2, the DRAKE system will be integrated with ships' Command and Control with optimized antennas for C-sUAS mission to
enhance ships' situational awareness and prosecution of UAS threats.

Prior to FY23, DRAKE C-UAS funding can be found in PE 0603654N/Project 3177.

