D. Acquisition Strategy
MACE is leveraging non-traditional industry investment to accelerate and achieve affordability, to minimize hypersonic weapon development and scale hypersonic
production timelines and cost. The maturity of technologies and investments to date will support a rapid transition to a program of record, minimize the development
timeline, and accelerate entry into production. This will be accomplished by continuing to leverage the SBIR competition utilizing the RCO authorities through the NRCC
to mature and field an early operational capability of an affordable mass munitions (Project Alpha) to close the warfighting gap before transitioning to the MACE POR.
Project Alpha will generate information used to enable the MACE acquisition strategy for an Initial and Full Operational Capability. Project Alpha has awarded a NAVAIR
originated Basic Ordering Agreement (BOA) under SBIR Phase III competitive efforts to execute multiple Delivery Orders (DO) to continue certification, integration,
and test of the weapon onto the F/A-18E/F platforms to support an accelerated scaled production and ultimate achievement of EOC in FY 2027. The NRCC will also
establish additional contracts to commence Reactive Material Warhead and Advanced Lethality Enhancement Developments.


