FY 2026 Plans:
The FY26 iteration of the FLEX Campaign is in development, with a target of 12 classified initiatives. Topics will
include unmanned systems, artificial intelligence, resilient communications, long range fires, C-ISR, contested
logistics, and maritime homeland defense. FLEX will emphasize examination and development of warfare center
technologies, thus enabling continued refinement via the USFF Fleet Battle Problem series and the PACFLT
Integrated Battle Problem series. Classified descriptions of FY26 FLEX initiatives are readily available at higher
classifications.
FY 2027 Base Plans:
The FY27 iteration of the FLEX Campaign is in development, with a target of 14 classified initiatives. Topics
are likely to include unmanned systems, artificial intelligence, resilient communications, long range fires,
counterintelligence, surveillance, and reconnaissance, contested logistics, and maritime homeland defense.
