D. Acquisition Strategy
OASuW-1 began using an accelerated acquisition approach, with streamlined governance to transition the DARPA/ONR-demonstrated Long Range Anti-Ship Missile
(LRASM) for use as an air-launched weapon from USAF and USN platforms. Under these processes, LRASM has completed development and test of baseline
capabilities and delivered an EOC on both USAF and USN platforms, while also initiating a capability improvements program (LRASM C-1), which has completed
Lots 1-7 production buys. In FY 2025, the program made the strategic decision to split LRASM C-1 and LRASM C-3 into subprograms, based on projected unit cost
differences and distinct positions in the acquisition pathway timeline. LRASM C-1 will cease formal acquisition reporting on production end in FY 2027. The program
established a new Acquisition Program Baseline (APB) in FY 2026.




