 inclement weather situations through hardware and software changes. This effort supports the Comprehensive Review and GAO Report recommendations to develop
 and implement V-22 mid-life upgrade efforts that will improve current readiness and safety performance outcomes.

FY 2027 funding for the Renewed V-22 Aircraft Modernization Program (ReVAMP) will enable the development of full and partial mitigation strategies to address and
downgrade open and monitored I-D and I-E SSRAs, while supporting the implementation of an integrated process to comprehensively identify, analyze, and mitigate
both system safety and non-system safety risks. This effort supports the Comprehensive Review and GAO Report recommendations to develop and implement V-22
mid-life upgrade efforts that will improve current readiness and safety performance outcomes.

JUSTIFICATION FOR BUDGET ACTIVITY: This program is funded under OPERATIONAL SYSTEMS DEVELOPMENT because it includes development efforts to
