FY 2025 Accomplishments: Mission and Collaborative Autonomy (MCA):

In FY25, key accomplishments included the delivery of a minimum viable product (MVP) enabling small
Unmanned Surface Vehicles (USVs) to collaboratively execute mission tasks in support of INDOPACOM
operational needs. The capability was successfully tested during an on-water demonstration, after which it
was transitioned to the Defense Innovation Unit's Autonomous Collaborative Teaming (DIU ACT) program for
further integration and experimentation. FY25 efforts also demonstrated the portability of the autonomy software
stack across multiple platforms, validating the ability to rapidly transition capabilities between different USV
classes. As part of this work, autonomy components were rapidly integrated and evaluated during multiple

                                                                                EHICLE ENABLING CAPABILITIES

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                   FY 2025   FY 2026
fleet exercises, including Autonomous Warrior, demonstrating the flexibility and operational relevance of the
autonomy architecture. Additionally, the autonomy stack developed for small USVs was provided to an industry
partner for integration on a medium-sized USV platform, further validating cross-platform applicability. Continued
maturation of the autonomy stack also enabled support for N2/N6 operational missions, including capabilities
relevant to Maritime Domain Awareness (MDA) and Intelligence, Surveillance, and Reconnaissance (ISR)
operations.

