Description: C2 ecosystem provides a resilient, multi-echelon command-and-control (C2) and orchestration
framework for large numbers of unmanned systems (UxS) across Maritime Operations Centers (MOCs), Joint
Operations Centers (JOCs), Unmanned Operations Centers (UOCs), and host platforms. This architecture
integrates data sources with UxS C2 networks, enabling operations and commanders at multiple echelons
to deploy high-level distributed unmanned mission in near-real time without the need to plan, task, monitor,
and dynamically retask individual assets. Through a unified C2 framework and data-broker layer, the system
supports one-to-many supervisory control of heterogenous UxS, synchronized with joint fires networks and
operational C2 systems. Resilient networking, redundant data pathways, and a common operational interface
fuse sensor data, autonomy status, and mission tasking into a coherent operational picture. This enterprise
C2 capability enables coordinated employment of masses unmanned systems across domains, shortening
decision cycles, increasing lethality and mission effectiveness, and reducing operator workload in contested
environments.

