These efforts include AN/ALQ-231(V) Intrepid Tiger II Family of Systems, Collaborative Electronic Warfare (EW)/EW Battle Management, and EW Service Architecture
(EWSA). These programs are the Marine Corps' initial steps to create systems to distribute EW capability across the battlespace.

