       Change Summary Explanation
       Cost: FY 2027 funding increased by $44.082 million to support continued development of priority Electronic Warfare (EW) system capabilities.

       Schedule:

       Project Unit 2175/Tactical Air Electronic Warfare:
       Systems Development:
       - Dual Band Decoy (DBD) added an Design Review 3 to 3QFY26 and DBD EMD contract extends from 4QFY26 to 2QFY28 due to additional engineering design
       adjustments. As a result, the program adjusted the timeline for test events to later in the FYDP. DT will now start 4QFY26 and complete 4QFY27. OT also
       shifted to begin 4QFY27 and complete in 4QFY28.
       - Adaptive Radar Countermeasures (ARC) development was discontinued 1QFY26 with funding being redirected to the higher Navy priority, Dual Band Decoy.
       - 1QFY27 Initiates infrastructure stand-up efforts to support Advanced Electronic Warfare (ADVEW) capabilities for the F/A-18E/F aircraft.
       Deliveries: ALQ-214 SRA extended from 4QFY26 to 3QFY27.

